<section>
<title>Detailed Description</title>

<para>The union representing <link linkend="_structevmc__result">evmc_result</link> &quot;optional storage&quot;. </para>



<para>The <link linkend="_structevmc__result">evmc_result</link> struct contains 24 bytes of optional storage that can be reused by the object creator if the object does not contain <link linkend="_structevmc__result_1ae7f37ff7c9cfa3b58af2c89f4d610522">evmc_result::create_address</link>.</para>

<para>A VM implementation MAY use this memory to keep additional data when returning result from <link linkend="_group__EVMC_1gaed9a4ab5609b55c5e3272d6d37d84ff7">evmc_execute_fn()</link>. The host application MAY use this memory to keep additional data when returning result of performed calls from <link linkend="_group__EVMC_1ga54f569386b52be6eee15ca9e14ed1ef8">evmc_call_fn()</link>.</para>

